Package: rigz
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Parallel gzip compressor written in Rust
 rigz is a drop-in replacement for gzip that uses multiple processors
 and cores for compression. It produces fully gzip-compatible output
 and achieves significant speedup on multi-core systems.
 .
 Features:
  - Parallel compression using all available CPU cores
  - Drop-in replacement for gzip (same command-line interface)
  - Cross-platform (Linux, macOS, Windows)
  - Based on pigz by Mark Adler
